channel.title: 2007 Remake (Kinda)
channel.description:
Hey MoparScape,
I'm looking to make a 2007 Remake, but not a complete remake. Just all skills 100%. All PvM 100% All PvP 100%. So, can someone please supply me a good source and client for this.
I've got no knowledge of hyperion so that isn't an option, I've got an emulous source but I just need a Emulous client that has head Icons, 377 Graphics, Animations, Items, Objects, Everything with the 377 Client gameframe. If someone can supply me with this I can start right away.
Also, can someone give me a link to all the RuneScape websites I can get information out of like skilling xp rates and everything. I can't find anything.
Thanks,
Skyro!

@Kidpaparoach wrote:

[quote=“baddy351, post:24, topic:436952”][quote author=Kidpaparoach link=topic=539667.msg3952804#msg3952804 date=1332449012]

Hyperion ain’t even hard to learn… I don’t get it, why you idiots want a unstable server instead of stable one, all it takes is a week of learning the new framework…or less.

Who are you calling an idiot you utter arsehole. You know nothing about us so in fact your an idiot for saying that.
Fucking dickhead
[/quote]
This is completely not needed. If anything, -nothing is right. Hyperion’s frameworking is alot more convenient. I can’t stand PI, and it takes months to learn where everything is because it was so horribly created. Hyperion is much easier to learn, and from a programmers aspect, is put together better. As far as how stable it is, hyperion is surprisingly not stable. A runescape server can hold a minimum of 2000 (Most can hold more), hyperion can hold like 700. (Far better than some). So obviously the networking needs some adjustment, and other things.[/quote]
I KNOW HYPERION IS BETTER, but fact is pi is easier to elarn for most. I’m not saying this due to my opinion i’m saying this from what I’ve seen people say collectively.
